festival.introText: A 3 day family-friendly festival in Dorset that aims to raise money with every ticket sold to fight children's cancer.
festival.location: Charisworth Farm Cottage in Blandford Forum

artists.name: DJ Sara Blow & Tor De Force

faqs.question: When is Teddy Rocks 2023?
faqs.answer: Teddy Rocks takes place Friday 28th April - Sunday 30th April 2023.

faqs.question: How to get to Teddy Rocks
faqs.answer: Teddy Rocks is held in Dorset at Charisworth Farm, Blandford Forum, DT11 9AL. Travel towards Winterborne Whitechurch on the A354 and follow the signs for the festival.

faqs.question: Where is Teddy Rocks?
faqs.answer: Teddy Rocks is located in Dorset at Charisworth Farm Cottage, Blandford Forum DT11 9AL.

faqs.question: Is there a shuttle bus to Teddy Rocks?
faqs.answer: Yes, a regular shuttle bus will be running from Blandford Town to and from the festival site.

faqs.question: Buses to Teddy Rocks
faqs.answer: There are bus services to Blandford and you can take the shuttle bus from there.

faqs.question: Trains to Teddy Rocks
faqs.answer: The nearest station is Poole and from there you can get a bus to Blandford and take the shuttle bus from there.

faqs.question: Cars to Teddy Rocks
faqs.answer: It's recommended that you park in Blandford and take the shuttle bus from there. Alternatively there will be limited parking at the festival that you will require a ticket for (separate from your festival ticket). They are allocated on a first come first serve basis and if you should leave and return during the festival your space will not be guaranteed for when you return.
